<div id="review_1885937545" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1885937545" />
    <a title="Campbell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7199941-campbell"><img alt="Campbell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609402680p2/7199941.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1885937545?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Campbell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Campbell" href="/user/show/7199941-campbell">Campbell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7199941-campbell?shelf=literary-fiction">literary-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7199941-campbell?shelf=audiobook">audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7199941-campbell?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7199941-campbell?shelf=great-literature-course">great-literature-course</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7199941-campbell?shelf=classic-literature">classic-literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1885937545" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3887201807218170613">What a novel! Never have I come across one, as far as I can recall, that so precisely understands the workings of thought processes, what motivates people and demonstrates how, given that understanding, people can be cynically manipulated to fulfill the wishes of others.<br/><br/>Also the Vicomte de Valmont is a fantastic character whose ability to take revenge knows few, if any, equals (Edmond Dantes, perhaps).</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

